<p>Whatever you land on, test it with your own numbers before you move everything across, and give yourself an easy way to get your data out later so you're never locked in. If you'd like to compare more options, our guides on the <a href="/best-quickbooks-alternatives/">best QuickBooks alternatives</a>, the <a href="/best-free-accounting-software-for-small-business/">best free accounting software for small business</a>, and the <a href="/cheapest-accounting-software-for-self-employed/">cheapest accounting software for the self-employed</a> come at the same question from different angles. The best tool is the one that fits your country, your products, and how you like to work, and sometimes that tool is the one you already have.</p>
